reut2-008.sgm, TAIWAN HOLDING TALKS WITH ADB, TAIWAN OFFICIAL, Taiwan is holding discussions with theAsian Development Bank (ADB) to try to settle a politicaldispute over its representation in the bank, a foreign ministryspokesman said.    Taiwan, one of the founders of the 47-member ADB, boycottedthe annual meeting last year to protest against a decision tochange its membership name to Taipei

