reut2-008.sgm, ARGYLL SELLS SUBSIDIARY'S ASSETS FOR 14 MLN STG, Food and drink retailer Argyll Group Plc&lt;AYLL.L> said it has agreed to sell its U.K. Subsidiary &lt;GeorgeMorton Ltd> to &lt;Seagram United Kingdom Ltd> for about 14 mlnstg in cash.    The consideration for Morton's fixed assets, stocks,debtors and goodwill is payable on completion of the sale. Thedisposal will bring Argyll an extraordinary credit of some 8.4mln stg.    Argyll added the agreements also depend on an indicationfrom the U.K. Office of Fair Trading by June 23 that the salewill not be referred to the Monopolies Commission. Argyllshares were up 12p to 440, firming before the announcement. REUTER&#3;
